3.1.20  2:32 pm   bill, your countdown timer cannot be called a timer if it goes down by a single unit using an inconsistent amount of days. i.e. 3 days -> 18, 1 day -> 17, 2 days -> 16
hate to break it to you but that is actually an objectiver rather than a timer, since time is irrelevant to the input

     that may be true

     and "objectiver" sounds gross
listen to that bill
"objectiver"
"i am having a countdown objectiver"
"the countdown objectiver is at 16"
listen to that
say it in your head again

     it's ok, i already did once. it makes no sense. the whole thing was your idea and i don't like it

     
"objectiver"
you don't want that bill

     what i don't want to do is call it that

     
you want a countdown timer

     that would be nice, but a little dicey considering the scope of the transition i am in

     
set it to 16 days from now or else we will all know you actually are having a countdown objectiver
